{"TopicId":191685,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Super small mun base","CreatedByName":"Hdeedose","CreatedById":201851,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-16T08:49:16Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Hdeedose","CreatedById":201851,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-16T08:49:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi , here is my challenge idea \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild a base on the Mun , but each piece should be carried in service bays(2.5m) . It ads a lot of difficulties , like the modules cannot be taller than 1.3m . \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E can be used , but only to connect\u00A0the station pieces together .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe base should \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E -Generate power\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0 -Contain at lease 2 kerbals\u00A0 -Have a 100% connection with Kerbin\u00A0 -Have at least 5 science things\u00A0 -Have at least 50 unities of monopropellant and oxidizer and 40 unities of liquid fuel\u00A0 -Have a kerbal-controlled rover\u00A0 -Have a docking port\u00A0 -Look cool .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think all is here ! I already have two modules on the Mun done . Here they are \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00221581842774-1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.22\u0022 height=\u0022575\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.noelshack.com/fichiers/2020/07/7/1581842774-1.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00221581842778-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.22\u0022 height=\u0022575\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.noelshack.com/fichiers/2020/07/7/1581842778-2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill a lot of work to do ... Let\u0027s see what YOU can do !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-16T11:57:42Z\u0022 title=\u002202/16/2020 11:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 16, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Hdeedose\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-16T17:25:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou make your base crew live in a coffin?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-16T17:39:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223742068\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191685\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581873923\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou make your base crew live in a coffin?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly if they\u0027re good bois.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hdeedose","CreatedById":201851,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-17T00:45:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223742068\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191685\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581873923\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou make your base crew live in a coffin?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223742073\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191685\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581874797\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly if they\u0027re good bois.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course ! Else , it wasn\u0027t fitting in the cargo bay (2.5m) . And I payed attention to close the coffin the best\u00A0 I could . There are no holes . The big advantage to do that is that I can fit two kerbals inside .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-17T00:50:42Z\u0022 title=\u002202/17/2020 12:50  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 17, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Hdeedose\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-17T02:56:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223741916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191685\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581842956\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201851\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hdeedose\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Hdeedose said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild a base on the Mun , but each piece should be carried in service bays(2.5m) . It ads a lot of difficulties , like the modules cannot be taller than 1.3m . \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E can be used , but only to connect\u00A0the station pieces together .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe base should \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E -Generate power\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0 -Contain at lease 2 kerbals\u00A0 -Have a 100% connection with Kerbin\u00A0 -Have at least 5 science things\u00A0 -Have at least 50 unities of monopropellant and oxidizer and 40 unities of liquid fuel\u00A0 -Have a kerbal-controlled rover\u00A0 -Have a docking port\u00A0 -Look cool .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably not entirely what you had in mind, but my first thought at reading this challenge was \u0027I wonder if I can do all of that with a single 2.5m service bay?\u0027\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI present the RoverBase 2.5:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/QY4EljoeIAk?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSurprisingly stable rover even on Kerbin, works well within the usual safeguards of lower gravity bodies. Easy to deliver to Mun or Minmus with a single 2.5m rocket stack.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221WU8mES.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.50\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/1WU8mES.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone else get a distinct \u0027Machines\u0027 vibe from this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Hz8DucE.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.50\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Hz8DucE.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll the comforts of home. Well, some of the comforts of home. Oh stop complaining or we\u0027ll dig out the Soyuz again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCraft file: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/swjr-swis/RoverBase-25\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/swjr-swis/RoverBase-25\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore pics: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/VYf1L3U\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/VYf1L3U\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-17T02:57:00Z\u0022 title=\u002202/17/2020 02:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 17, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by swjr-swis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eforum editing glitches\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flying dutchman","CreatedById":189896,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-17T13:40:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have discovered that it is actually possible to put a MK1 passenger cabin in a 2.5m storage Bay. And if you use pistons you can get it out of there as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-17T13:41:50Z\u0022 title=\u002202/17/2020 01:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 17, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Flying dutchman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hdeedose","CreatedById":201851,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-17T14:33:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223742300\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191685\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581908161\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably not entirely what you had in mind, but my first thought at reading this challenge was \u0027I wonder if I can do all of that with a single 2.5m service bay?\u0027\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI present the RoverBase 2.5:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/QY4EljoeIAk?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSurprisingly stable rover even on Kerbin, works well within the usual safeguards of lower gravity bodies. Easy to deliver to Mun or Minmus with a single 2.5m rocket stack.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/1WU8mES.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00221WU8mES.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.50\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/1WU8mES.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone else get a distinct \u0027Machines\u0027 vibe from this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Hz8DucE.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Hz8DucE.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.50\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Hz8DucE.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll the comforts of home. Well, some of the comforts of home. Oh stop complaining or we\u0027ll dig out the Soyuz again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCraft file: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/swjr-swis/RoverBase-25\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/swjr-swis/RoverBase-25\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore pics: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/VYf1L3U\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/VYf1L3U\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was absolutely not what I had in mind , but (almost) that\u0027s right ! All is in there , except that some parts are outside . But I think you can easily get rid of the wheels and put extendable solar panels inside the cargo bay . But mor me , it is \u0022Mission accomplished\u0022 !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Moncasta","CreatedById":202736,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-17T16:24:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHAHAHA it does look like a coffin!! This is so funny\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hdeedose","CreatedById":201851,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-18T15:40:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo , I finally finished my base (well , almost because \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is still not updated for 1.9)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFuel module (bottom left) and docking port and rover (docked together) in the middle .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221582039849-1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.22\u0022 height=\u0022575\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.noelshack.com/fichiers/2020/08/2/1582039849-1.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Cs\u003Ecoffin\u003C/s\u003E command pod was replaced and now have legs and a ladder .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221582039934-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.22\u0022 height=\u0022575\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.noelshack.com/fichiers/2020/08/2/1582039934-2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s better than a service bay to do a rover ? This thing weights 0.7 T and can go to 10 m/s on Kerbin .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221582039958-3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.22\u0022 height=\u0022575\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://image.noelshack.com/fichiers/2020/08/2/1582039958-3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think I finished my challenge ! That was not very hard (mostly long) and I learned how to land in a specific spot . That\u0027s all right for me !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-19T00:39:52Z\u0022 title=\u002202/19/2020 12:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 19, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Hdeedose\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kspnerd122","CreatedById":199169,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-25T00:33:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis DLC allowed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hdeedose","CreatedById":201851,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-25T00:52:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223746801\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191685\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582590826\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199169\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kspnerd122\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, kspnerd122 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis DLC allowed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo , with it , it is too easy !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-25T00:53:02Z\u0022 title=\u002202/25/2020 12:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 25, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Hdeedose\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kspnerd122","CreatedById":199169,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-25T10:23:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean Making History not Breaking Ground\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hdeedose","CreatedById":201851,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-25T11:04:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223746962\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191685\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582626217\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199169\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kspnerd122\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, kspnerd122 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean Making History not Breaking Ground\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes , you can use the Making history , that\u0027s fine .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}